176
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,660
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Please understand, Yura.</font>

177
00:12:12,170 --> 00:12:14,810
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No! Stop!</font>

178
00:12:15,680 --> 00:12:17,980
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hanna! Please!</font>

179
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:22,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Stop!</font>

180
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hanna?</font>

181
00:12:33,770 --> 00:12:36,610
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hanna! Hanna!</font>

182
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:41,570
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Was she going to use the syringe to drain 
her blood and the knife to carve her up?</font>

183
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:46,820
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Was there anything unusual about 
the woman before she attacked you?</font>

184
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:53,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Now that you mention it, she'd seemed 
to be researching something recently.</font>

185
00:12:55,330 --> 00:12:56,630
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What are you looking at?</font>

186
00:12:58,740 --> 00:12:59,590
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nothing.</font>

187
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:03,550
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A nautical chart?</font>

188
00:13:06,620 --> 00:13:11,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Say, Yura. Are you sure
you're the only mermaid left?</font>

189
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:12,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

190
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:13,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't you have friends?</font>

191
00:13:14,170 --> 00:13:17,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't you know where
 to find other mermaids?</font>

192
00:13:18,790 --> 00:13:20,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No, I don't.</font>

193
00:13:21,330 --> 00:13:22,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are you sure?</font>

194
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,780
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26"><i>After that, Hanna stopped talking to me.</i></font>

195
00:13:30,770 --> 00:13:33,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She must have been 
searching for mermaids.</font>

196
00:13:33,450 --> 00:13:38,220
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Perhaps she was planning to build
 a harem of mermaids. Dirty girl.</font>

197
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:40,290
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">More like eat 'em all alive.</font>

198
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:45,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No... So Hanna really did mean to do it?</font>

199
00:13:57,620 --> 00:13:59,180
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Are you feeling okay?</font>

200
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm so sorry.</font>

201
00:14:02,820 --> 00:14:05,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But I'm glad I at least 
threw up in the tank.</font>

202
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:09,160
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Uh, y-you are?</font>

203
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I-I'll help you clean it later.</font>

204
00:14:12,290 --> 00:14:14,330
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you. You're very kind.</font>

205
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I really shouldn't be doing this.</font>

206
00:14:22,140 --> 00:14:25,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I keep saying I want to 
understand her reasons, but...</font>

207
00:14:25,900 --> 00:14:27,510
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why shouldn't you?</font>

208
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I had been alone for a long time.</font>

209
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:33,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'd gotten separated from my pod
 a very long time before.</font>

210
00:14:33,990 --> 00:14:36,340
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And I was so lonely.</font>

211
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:40,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But then, Hanna made me a promise.</font>

212
00:14:47,330 --> 00:14:48,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What's wrong, Yura?</font>

213
00:14:48,940 --> 00:14:51,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't know. I just feel so happy.</font>

214
00:14:51,950 --> 00:14:57,210
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I never knew my heart 
could feel this full.</font>

215
00:14:58,740 --> 00:15:01,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I can't help but laugh.</font>

216
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:04,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And I know that's because I'm with you.</font>

217
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,280
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hanna?</font>

218
00:15:12,280 --> 00:15:14,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Let's get married, Yura.</font>

219
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:15,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

220
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:28,700
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I, Hanna, hereby swear to love you
 for all eternity, Yurate.</font>

221
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:30,960
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">All eternity?</font>

222
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:34,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes, all eternity. As in forever.</font>

223
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,070
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Forever?</font>

224
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:40,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">"Forever" it is.</font>

225
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:01,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I lied. I don't want to know why.</font>

226
00:16:02,590 --> 00:16:04,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yurate?</font>

227
00:16:04,270 --> 00:16:09,090
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The truth is, I probably just want
 to hear someone tell me</font>

228
00:16:09,090 --> 00:16:11,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">that Hanna wasn't actually
 trying to kill me.</font>

229
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:14,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But why did this happen?</font>

230
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:17,050
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I want to know, but I'm also scared.</font>

231
00:16:17,050 --> 00:16:19,240
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Maybe it's best if I never find out.</font>

232
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">No, that isn't right.</font>

233
00:16:21,660 --> 00:16:26,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You cared about her that much, 
but you'd rather not know what happened?</font>

234
00:16:26,430 --> 00:16:28,170
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't believe that at all.</font>

235
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:34,260
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I know it's scary, but knowing what 
happened should bring you peace,</font>

236
00:16:34,730 --> 00:16:36,360
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and help you find a way to move on.</font>

237
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:43,270
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I want to believe Hanna 
was sincere in her promise.</font>

238
00:16:44,260 --> 00:16:48,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Even if she swore eternal love,</font>

239
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:50,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">compared to an immortal mermaid,</font>

240
00:16:50,950 --> 00:16:53,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">a human life would pass by
 in the blink of an eye.</font>

241
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:59,750
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I'm sure it must be terrible to die first,
 leaving your loved one behind.</font>

242
00:16:59,750 --> 00:17:01,990
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Mermaids aren't immortal.</font>

243
00:17:01,990 --> 00:17:02,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

244
00:17:03,310 --> 00:17:08,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">They certainly live much longer 
than humans, but they're mortal.</font>

245
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,840
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What? But I was sure...</font>

246
00:17:12,790 --> 00:17:15,880
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Bring her in here, Lynn Reinweiß.</font>

247
00:17:23,870 --> 00:17:26,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">My original hypothesis still stands.</font>

248
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:31,900
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The woman assaulted the mermaid 
because she wanted to become immortal.</font>

249
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:38,530
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But you said there was no point in living 
together if she just wanted to kill her.</font>

250
00:17:38,530 --> 00:17:43,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There was a point. 
That was the woman's ultimate goal.</font>

251
00:17:44,150 --> 00:17:45,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Goal?</font>

252
00:17:45,730 --> 00:17:50,000
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">The woman wanted to continue 
living with the mermaid,</font>

253
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:52,130
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">so she tried to eat her.</font>

254
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:53,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Huh?</font>

255
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,760
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">But that would defeat the purpose.</font>

256
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,970
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yup, sure would. Unless...</font>

257
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:01,430
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What if that woman believed
mermaids were immortal, too?</font>

258
00:18:03,150 --> 00:18:05,710
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She's 200 years old,
 but just look at her.</font>

259
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:08,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">It wouldn't be unusual for a human
 to assume she's immortal.</font>

260
00:18:08,850 --> 00:18:09,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Don't you agree?</font>

261
00:18:11,020 --> 00:18:11,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Yes.</font>

262
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:15,830
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">And the syringe the woman 
used during the crime</font>

263
00:18:15,830 --> 00:18:18,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">likely wasn't meant 
for draining her blood.</font>

264
00:18:18,730 --> 00:18:22,910
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Only someone like you, Lynn Reinweiß, 
would jump to a conclusion like that.</font>

265
00:18:23,410 --> 00:18:25,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">There are many other possibilities.</font>

266
00:18:25,450 --> 00:18:28,370
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Taking a blood sample, poisoning her,
 giving her an anesthetic...</font>

267
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:33,470
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Maybe she wanted to make the procedure 
as painless as possible for the mermaid.</font>

268
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:35,740
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">She was gonna eat her, after all.</font>

269
00:18:35,740 --> 00:18:37,380
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Why would she bother doing that?</font>

270
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:39,440
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I need to ask one thing first.</font>

271
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:42,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">How much time did you 
spend with the woman?</font>

272
00:18:42,570 --> 00:18:45,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">I don't know. I wasn't counting.</font>

273
00:18:45,690 --> 00:18:48,850
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Maybe half of a hundred years?
 Or a little more?</font>

274
00:18:48,850 --> 00:18:52,940
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">A <i>hundred</i>? But you said 
you were only together a short while.</font>

275
00:18:53,870 --> 00:18:55,150
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">That isn't very long.</font>

276
00:18:57,900 --> 00:19:00,110
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Different species 
experience time differently.</font>

277
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:06,080
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">In the mermaid's eyes, the woman likely
looked the same as when they met.</font>

278
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:09,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">However, time had surely taken its toll.</font>

279
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:35,560
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Nearing the end of her life,</font>

280
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:39,230
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">the woman was probably afraid of dying 
and leaving the mermaid behind.</font>

281
00:19:40,370 --> 00:19:42,950
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">If she died, the mermaid 
would be alone again.</font>

282
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:46,690
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">So she decided to use the mermaid's flesh
 to become immortal</font>

283
00:19:46,690 --> 00:19:48,450
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">and continue living together,</font>

284
00:19:49,370 --> 00:19:51,870
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">thereby fulfilling her promise
 of eternal love.</font>

285
00:19:52,910 --> 00:19:54,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">B-But...</font>

286
00:19:54,680 --> 00:19:57,460
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">"It must be terrible to die first, 
leaving your loved one behind."</font>

287
00:19:57,460 --> 00:19:59,030
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Those were your words.</font>

288
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:07,020
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Hanna.</font>

289
00:20:08,560 --> 00:20:09,720
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What a relief.</font>

290
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,730
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Thank you.</font>

291
00:20:20,570 --> 00:20:24,490
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Love can take many forms. 
Isn't that what makes it wonderful?</font>

292
00:20:25,950 --> 00:20:30,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Sometimes, I have trouble 
understanding the way people think.</font>

293
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,420
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Also, those two will never—</font>

294
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:33,250
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Uh-huh?</font>

295
00:20:34,850 --> 00:20:37,500
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">You're so cute when you're sad, Lynn.</font>

296
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:42,140
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">What does <i>that</i> have to do 
with what I was just saying?</font>

297
00:20:48,340 --> 00:20:50,580
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">One sip of mermaid blood.</font>

298
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:54,520
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">How silly.</font>

299
00:21:07,930 --> 00:21:09,410
<font face="Roboto Medium" size="26">Am I...</font>

